devdoc.author: Cory Gabrielsen (cory.eth)
devdoc.details: This contract is responsible for rendering an Avatar based on its DNA.      Avatars are rendered as 32x32 RGBA images with transparency around      the Avatar's body. Avatars are rendered using hand-drawn, original art      created by the contract author (one pixel at a time with a ball mouse). Immutable: Once initialized, the contract is immutable. Art stored in OpenAvatarGen0Assets is immutable (append-only storage). So, rendering is deterministic. Gas: Due to PNG encoding, rendering may cost 10,000,000+ gas. With further base64 encoding (i.e. token URI), combined rendering and encoding may cost 15,000,000+ gas. Terminology: - Canvas Id (uint8): Selects from an array of canvases - Layer Index (uint8): Selects from an array of layers for a given canvas - Pattern Index (uint8): Selects from an array of patterns for a given layer - Palette Index (uint8): Selects from an array of palettes for a given                          pattern - Color Index (uint8): Selects from an array of colors for a given palette - Color (bytes4): RGBA Structure: - Every layer contains an array of selectable patterns. - Each pattern references a specific palette code. - Each palette code corresponds to an array of palettes. - Each pattern (uncompressed) is a 32x32=1024 array of color indices.      - compressed as [height, width, offsetX, offsetY, bytes]  -Each palette is an array of RGBA (bytes4[]) which always starts with   0x00000000 (transparent). - So, a color index of 0x00 is transparent. - In essence, each byte in a pattern is a color index which defines an   RGBA color in the corresponding palette array to draw for that pixel. Rendering: Layers are drawn one over another, from lowest to highest layer index, with alpha-blending. The 32-byte Avatar DNA is interpretted to as defining the pattern and palette for each layer. Pixels are drawn based on color derived from DNA-encoded pattern and palette index. If a DNA defines an invalid index, the layer is drawn as transparent. DNA: It should be noted that while OpenAvatar DNA is interpretted here as implicitly defining asset references for drawing the Avatar, the concept of DNA is designed as a standalone building block. Application-specific re-interpretations of OpenAvatar DNA are entirely possible and encouraged. Encoding: Avatars are rendered as base64-encoded PNGs, embedded within an SVG. The SVG embeds the PNG as a <foreignObject>, chosen due to Safari's lack of support (bug?) for "image-rendering: pixelated" of <image> elements within SVGs.

claimReverseENS(address,address).details: Transfers ownership of the reverse ENS record associated with the      contract.

params.claimant: The address to set as the owner of the reverse record in                 ENS.

returns._0: The ENS node hash of the reverse record.

params.canvasId: The id of the canvas to use
params.layerPatternPalette: The layer, pattern, and palette to use for each layer

drawLayer(bytes,uint8,uint8,uint8,uint8).details: Overlay a layer on top of the image

params.canvasId: The id of the canvas to use
params.image: The image to overlay the layer on top of
params.layer: The index of the layer to overlay
params.palette: The index of the palette to use for the layer/pattern
params.pattern: The index of the pattern to use for the layer

drawLayerComposition(bytes,uint8,(uint8,.details: Draw a layer composition onto the image

params.canvasId: The id of the canvas to use
params.layerPatternPalette: The layer, pattern, and palette to use for each layer
params.out: The image to draw the layer composition onto

params.canvasId: The id of the canvas to use
params.image: The image to overlay the layer on top of
params.layer: The index of the layer to overlay
params.mask: The mask to apply to the pattern before overlaying it
params.palette: The index of the palette to use for the layer/pattern
params.pattern: The index of the pattern to use for the layer

params.pattern: The pattern to use for the layer

encodeIHDR(uint256,uint256,bool).details: Generates an IHDR chunk for a PNG image with the given width and height. This function generates an IHDR chunk according to the PNG specification (http://libpng.org/pub/png/spec/1.2/PNG-Chunks.html#C.IHDR).

params.alpha: Whether the image has alpha transparency.

returns._0: A bytes memory array containing the IDAT chunk data.

params.width: The width of the image, in pixels

params.openAvatarGen0Assets_: The address of the asset store read interface contract.

returns._0: True if the contract has been initialized, false otherwise.

openAvatar().details: This is a sentinel function to indicate that this contract is an OpenAvatar contract.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

returns._0: The byte array of the image.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setReverseENS(address,string).details: Sets the reverse ENS record associated with the contract.

params.name: The name to set as the reverse record in ENS.

returns._0: The ENS node hash of the reverse record.

params.interfaceId: The interface identifier, as specified in ERC-165.

returns._0: True if the contract supports interfaceID, false otherwise.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

CANVAS_ID.details: The canvas ID for the default, front-facing Avatar pose.

Gabrielsen (cory.eth)","details":"This contract is responsible for rendering an Avatar based on its DNA.      Avatars are rendered as 32x32 RGBA images with transparency around      the Avatar's body. Avatars are rendered using hand-drawn, original art      created by the contract author (one pixel at a time with a ball mouse). Immutable: Once initialized, the contract is immutable. Art stored in OpenAvatarGen0Assets is immutable (append-only storage). So, rendering is deterministic. Gas: Due to PNG encoding, rendering may cost 10,000,000+ gas. With further base64 encoding (i.e. token URI), combined rendering and encoding may cost 15,000,000+ gas. Terminology: - Canvas Id (uint8): Selects from an array of canvases - Layer Index (uint8): Selects from an array of layers for a given canvas - Pattern Index (uint8): Selects from an array of patterns for a given layer - Palette Index (uint8): Selects from an array of palettes for a given                          pattern - Color Index (uint8): Selects from an array of colors for a given palette - Color (bytes4): RGBA Structure: - Every layer contains an array of selectable patterns. - Each pattern references a specific palette code. - Each palette code corresponds to an array of palettes. - Each pattern (uncompressed) is a 32x32=1024 array of color indices.      - compressed as [height, width, offsetX, offsetY, bytes]  -Each palette is an array of RGBA (bytes4[]) which always starts with   0x00000000 (transparent). - So, a color index of 0x00 is transparent. - In essence, each byte in a pattern is a color index which defines an   RGBA color in the corresponding palette array to draw for that pixel. Rendering: Layers are drawn one over another, from lowest to highest layer index, with alpha-blending. The 32-byte Avatar DNA is interpretted to as defining the pattern and palette for each layer. Pixels are drawn based on color derived from DNA-encoded pattern and palette index. If a DNA defines an invalid index, the layer is drawn as transparent. DNA: It should be noted that while OpenAvatar DNA is interpretted here as implicitly defining asset references for drawing the Avatar, the concept of DNA is designed as a standalone building block. Application-specific re-interpretations of OpenAvatar DNA are entirely possible and encouraged. Encoding: Avatars are rendered as base64-encoded PNGs, embedded within an SVG. The SVG embeds the PNG as a <foreignObject>, chosen due to Safari's lack of support (bug?) for \"image-rendering: pixelated\" of <image> elements within devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}. This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier `onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to the owner.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

This contract is only required for intermediate, library-like contracts.

The bytes represent the following:  ZZZZ YYYY XXXX WWWW VVVV UUUU TTTT SSSS  0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000    Bytes  |  Chars  | Description  ---------|---------|-------------   [0:1]   | [0:3]   |  body   [2:3]   | [4:7]   |  tattoos   [4:5]   | [8:11]  |  makeup   [6:7]   | [12:15] |  left eye   [8:9]   | [16:19] |  right eye   [10:11] | [20:23] |  bottomwear   [12:13] | [24:27] |  footwear   [14:15] | [28:31] |  topwear   [16:17] | [32:35] |  handwear   [18:19] | [36:39] |  outerwear   [20:21] | [40:43] |  jewelry   [22:23] | [44:47] |  facial hair   [24:25] | [48:51] |  facewear   [26:27] | [52:55] |  eyewear   [28:29] | [56:59] |  hair   [30:31] | [60:63] |  reserved  Each 2-byte section is a struct of the following:    [0] | [0:1] |  pattern    [1] | [2:3] |  palette The pattern is an index into the pattern array. The palette is an index into the palette array.

devdoc.details: This contract is used to claim reverse ENS records.

claimReverseENS(address,address).details: Transfers ownership of the reverse ENS record associated with the      contract.

params.claimant: The address to set as the owner of the reverse record in                 ENS.

returns._0: The ENS node hash of the reverse record.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setReverseENS(address,string).details: Sets the reverse ENS record associated with the contract.

params.name: The name to set as the reverse record in ENS.

returns._0: The ENS node hash of the reverse record.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.details: KeepAlive is a contract designed to maintain its onchain presence in case of state expiration by using payable receive() and fallback() functions, while allow the owner to still withdraw funds. fallback():   - Default function that gets executed when no other function in the contract     matches the provided function signature, or when the contract receives     Ether along with data   - Can be payable or non-payable   - Must be marked external receive():   - Introduced in Solidity 0.6.0   - Special function that is executed when a contract receives Ether without     any data   - Must be payable   - Must be marked external   - Makes it easier to differentiate between intended Ether transfers and     other function calls

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.details: PNG is a contract for generating PNG images from raw image data in Solidity. It includes functions for encoding and decoding PNG images, as well as for calculating Adler32 and CRC32 checksums. This contract is based on the PNG specification: http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/spec/1.2/PNG-Contents.html It supports only 8 bit images and supports RGB or RGBA color formats. It uses compression method 0, filter method 0, and interlace method 0.

encodeIHDR(uint256,uint256,bool).details: Generates an IHDR chunk for a PNG image with the given width and height. This function generates an IHDR chunk according to the PNG specification (http://libpng.org/pub/png/spec/1.2/PNG-Chunks.html#C.IHDR).

params.alpha: Whether the image has alpha transparency.

returns._0: A bytes memory array containing the IDAT chunk data.

params.alpha: Whether the image has an alpha channel
params.height: The height of the image, in pixels
params.width: The width of the image, in pixels

IEND().notice: The IEND chunk marks the end of the PNG datastream. It contains no data. The IEND chunk must appear last. It is an error to place any data after the IEND chunk. The IEND chunk is always equal to 12 bytes 00 00 00 00 49 45 4e 44 ae 42 60 82

devdoc.details: This contract composes layer patterns into a single image.A pattern is a 2d byte array with a corresponding color palette.The values of the pattern array are indexes into the color palette.

AlreadyInitialized().details: Error reverted when the component is already initialized.

InterfaceUnsupported(address,bytes4).details: Error reverted when provided address does not support the required interface.

InvalidCanvasBytesPerPixel().details: Error reverted when the canvas bytes per pixel is not 4.

InvalidCanvasSize(uint8,uint256).details: Error reverted when the canvas size is invalid.

InvalidMaskLength(uint256,uint256).details: Error reverted when the mask length is invalid.

params.canvasId: The id of the canvas to use
params.layerPatternPalette: The layer, pattern, and palette to use for each layer

params.canvasId: The id of the canvas to use
params.image: The image to overlay the layer on top of
params.layer: The index of the layer to overlay
params.palette: The index of the palette to use for the layer/pattern
params.pattern: The index of the pattern to use for the layer

params.layerPatternPalette: The layer, pattern, and palette to use for each layer

params.pattern: The index of the pattern to use for the layer

params.palette: The palette to use for the layer/pattern
params.pattern: The pattern to use for the layer

NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.interfaceId: The interface identifier, as specified in ERC-165.

returns._0: True if the contract supports interfaceID, false otherwise.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
